Here's a comprehensive solution for the CSIR-SERC recruitment application, designed with all your requirements in mind. I'll provide the key implementation details, database structure, and critical code snippets.

---

### **System Architecture Overview**
- **Frontend**: Tailwind CSS (v3.3) + Alpine.js for dynamic UI
- **Backend**: PHP 8.2 (Modern OOP approach)
- **Database**: MariaDB 11 (with InnoDB)
- **Compliance**: CSIR Recruitment Guidelines + Government Compliance (GIGW)
- **Key Features**: Multi-lab support, multi-vacancy management, PDF generation, Telegram/SMTP notifications

---

### **Database Schema (MariaDB 11)**
```sql
CREATE DATABASE csir_serc_recruitment;
USE csir_serc_recruitment;

-- Labs (CSIR Labs)
CREATE TABLE labs (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    description TEXT,
    address TEXT,
    contact VARCHAR(50)
);

-- Recruitment Posts
CREATE TABLE posts (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    title VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    description TEXT,
    minimum_qualification VARCHAR(255),
    eligibility_criteria TEXT
);

-- Projects (Linked to vacancies)
CREATE TABLE projects (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    lab_id INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (lab_id) REFERENCES labs(id)
);

-- Vacancies (Multiple vacancies per post)
CREATE TABLE vacancies (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    lab_id INT NOT NULL,
    post_id INT NOT NULL,
    project_id INT,
    vacancies INT NOT NULL,
    deadline DATE NOT NULL,
    status ENUM('open','closed') DEFAULT 'open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (lab_id) REFERENCES labs(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (post_id) REFERENCES posts(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (project_id) REFERENCES projects(id)
);

-- Applicants
CREATE TABLE applicants (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    email VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    phone VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    gender ENUM('M','F','O') NOT NULL,
    dob DATE NOT NULL,
    profile_photo VARCHAR(255) NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- Applications
CREATE TABLE applications (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    vacancy_id INT NOT NULL,
    applicant_id INT NOT NULL,
    status ENUM('draft','submitted','processed','rejected','selected') DEFAULT 'draft',
    submission_date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    last_updated TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (vacancy_id) REFERENCES vacancies(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (applicant_id) REFERENCES applicants(id)
);

-- Education Details
CREATE TABLE education (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    applicant_id INT NOT NULL,
    degree VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    institution VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    year INT NOT NULL,
    percentage DECIMAL(5,2),
    document VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (applicant_id) REFERENCES applicants(id)
);

-- Publications
CREATE TABLE publications (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    applicant_id INT NOT NULL,
    title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    journal VARCHAR(255),
    year INT NOT NULL,
    doi VARCHAR(255),
    document VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (applicant_id) REFERENCES applicants(id)
);

-- Documents (Other required documents)
CREATE TABLE documents (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    application_id INT NOT NULL,
    document_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    file_path VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (application_id) REFERENCES applications(id)
);
```

---

### **Key Implementation Highlights**

#### 1. **Admin Panel (Core Features)**
```php
// admin/dashboard.php
<?php
require 'includes/auth.php'; // Handles admin login
require 'includes/db.php';

// Vacancy Management
if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'POST' && isset($_POST['create_vacancy'])) {
    $lab_id = $_POST['lab_id'];
    $post_id = $_POST['post_id'];
    $project_id = $_POST['project_id'] ?? null;
    $vacancies = $_POST['vacancies'];
    $deadline = $_POST['deadline'];

    $stmt = $pdo->prepare("INSERT INTO vacancies (lab_id, post_id, project_id, vacancies, deadline) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)");
    $stmt->execute([$lab_id, $post_id, $project_id, $vacancies, $deadline]);
    $success = "Vacancy created successfully!";
}

// PDF Generation
if (isset($_GET['download_pdf']) && is_numeric($_GET['id'])) {
    require 'vendor/autoload.php';
    use Dompdf\Dompdf;

    $app_id = $_GET['id'];
    $app = getApplicationDetails($app_id); // Custom function to fetch data

    $html = renderApplicationPDF($app); // Custom PDF template

    $dompdf = new Dompdf();
    $dompdf->loadHtml($html);
    $dompdf->setPaper('A4', 'portrait');
    $dompdf->render();
    $dompdf->stream("Application_{$app_id}.pdf", ['Attachment' => true]);
    exit;
}
?>
```

